1.2,71.2,70.79,71.24,71.32,70.94,71.05,69.86,69.95,69.52,71.64,71.33,72.12,72.94,71.97,72.12,73.44,74.64,73.44,74.21,73.53,73.88,72.98,74.33,73.9,76.49,76.94,76.44,76.63,75.74,75.46,76.34,77.84,77.85,76.84,76.8,77.79,78.16,81.12,82.27,82.53,83.76,85.66,84.33,85.68,86.5,86.82,88.68,86.42,91.4,94.46,93.22,91.16,90.43,91.16,88.8,85.84,83.83,81.88,84.85,87.83,86.32,89.24,87.62,88.7,88.23,89.4,92.97,92.24,92.35,91.45,94.79,93.92,96.81,96.01,95.31,93.17,93.25,94.68,93.53,93.32,93.44,95.0,95.54,99.46]}}},"industry":null,"sector_index":null,"rs_sector":null,"formulas":{"returns":"Trailing point return = price[t] / price[t-N] - 1 (N = 21/63/126/252 trading days); adjusted total-return prices.","dist_from_52w_high":"price[t] / max(price, last 252d) - 1 (how far below the 1-year peak).","dma":"price[t] / mean(price, last N days) - 1; 'above' = price >= the N-day average.","drawdown":"current = price[t]/running-peak - 1; maxDD = min(price/cummax - 1) over the window.","liquidity":"median daily traded value (turnover \u00f7 1e7 = \u20b9 cr) over the last ~21 trading days.","relative_strength":"horizon: stock return - benchmark return (pp); line: (stock/benchmark) rebased to 100 over the last year."},"notes":{"source":"adjusted total-return price panel (bhavcopy-reconstructed) + NSE index TR + bhavcopy turnover.","frequency":"daily","confidence":"high where history is long; flagged low if thin/short.","why_useful":"what the market is saying about the stock \u2014 trend, leadership vs the index/sector, and tradeability.","why_it_can_fail":"corporate-action gaps, illiquid names, or a short listing history can distort returns/DMA/RS."}},"business":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"flags":[{"label":"Business quality","value":75.0,"unit":"/100","status":"good","read":"High-quality business (75/100).","meaning":"Composite of profitability, return on capital, balance-sheet safety and cash conversion (the Fundamentals-tab Quality score).","why_useful":"A durable, high-return business compounds value; a low-quality one needs a bigger margin of safety.","why_it_can_fail":"A single composite can mask a weak component; open the Fundamentals tab for the breakdown."},{"label":"Cash conversion","value":-0.62,"unit":"\u00d7","status":"weak","read":"Only -0.62\u00d7 \u2014 profit not turning into cash (watch receivables/inventory).","meaning":"Median of (cash from operations \u00f7 net profit) over the last 5 years.","why_useful":"Profit you can't collect as cash is fragile; >0.8\u00d7 means earnings are real cash, <0.6\u00d7 is an accrual red flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":0.61,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"ok","read":"Moderate leverage (D/E 0.61\u00d7, interest cover 3.3\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":7.32,"unit":"% YoY","status":"ok","read":"Profit up 7% YoY \u2014 modest.","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":20.9,"pe_percentile":95.0,"median_pe":16.7,"earnings_yield_pct":4.78,"pb":3.02,"ev_ebitda":13.29,"quality_score":75.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":22.5,"peg":0.93,"cheapness":{"status":"weak","read":"P/E at the 95-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 expensive vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 20.9\u00d7 earnings for ~23% 5-yr profit CAGR, the market is paying \u22480.93\u00d7 growth (PEG). >2 = a lot already priced in; <1 = cheap if growth holds. This PEG divides TTM P/E by TRAILING 5-year annual PAT CAGR (endpoint-to-endpoint) \u2014 a time-axis mismatch vs the textbook FORWARD-EPS PEG, and one abnormal base/terminal year distorts the CAGR. A rough trailing valuation-vs-growth gauge, not a precise forward PEG.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[82.05,82.05,82.05,82.05,82.05,82.05,82.05],"latest_pct":82.05,"chg_1y_pp":0.0},"FII":{"periods":["Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[2.97,1.58,1.47,1.81,2.48,2.9,3.14],"latest_pct":3.14,"chg_1y_pp":1.67},"DII":{"periods":["Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[6.88,7.67,8.23,7.33,5.67,5.08,5.37],"latest_pct":5.37,"chg_1y_pp":-2.86},"Public":{"periods":["Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[8.09,8.7,8.25,8.8,9.79,9.96,9.44],"latest_pct":9.44,"chg_1y_pp":1.19}},"pledge":null,"events":[{"date":"23-Sep-2024","subject":"Dividend - Re 0.50 Per Share","materiality":"Low"}],"placeholders":[{"label":"Promoter pledge (detail)","note":"share-level pl